Transcription.Text: The kind of good preached by Kant and Coleridge seemed to him vague and undefined. But everyone knew what pleasure was. Here was a goal with no mystical nonsense about it. Of Christ as in some sense continuing his work of redemption by endlessly offering himself to God in organic Union with his members.
